### Step 1: Find the coordinates of point \(P\)
Point \(P\) is the third vertex of the equilateral triangle \(ABP\). The side length of the equilateral triangle is 1. The coordinates of \(P\) can be found by rotating point \(B\) around point \(A\) by \(60^\circ\) counterclockwise. Using the rotation matrix for \(60^\circ\):
\[
